Anonymous Tue 11 Sep 2018 21:41:43 No.18227392 Report
Quoted By: >>18227505
>>18227306
There's probably a few million websites on the internet about 'how to write thing' now.

But start with a short list. At the top of the list, what happens at the beginning. At the bottom of the list, how it ends. Now start adding things into the middle that need to happen to connect A and B. Start with scenes (if there's more than one) then start breaking each scene down with its own list of what needs to happen in that scene.

Add more details as you think of them. May end up deciding some lines can be put together into one paragraph, others will need a paragraph of their own.
Anonymous
  • Post
  • Report

Anonymous Tue 11 Sep 2018 21:42:37 No.18227408 Report
Quoted By: >>18227505
>>18227306
>Can any write flags give me tips

Just start. Mistakes will happen and while it's important to keep an eye out for them and read through your stuff after finishing to keep an eye out for any mistakes, say a day after writing to come at it with a fresh mind, sometimes it just happens. If posters give feedback, either politely or screaming shit in your ear, best take it well and see how to improve through it.

There's way more specific and important tips and information, but this is the most general advice I can give. Just start, try to avoid mistakes, but know there will be mistakes even if you went through the whole thing with a magnifying glass.

Establish intent, if its lewd or just comfy. Make a storyline of events and "triggers" that lead to the next scene/mood.

Do you start off alone or with someone? Do you want em to fug in any particular place? Do you want them to meet someplace and then start something there? You need a conector in there, you need the core ideas of what you wanna write and then kinda just fill out the blanks.

Make a list of what you want to happen, your intent, then make a rough timeline. Write the inbetweens to your liking.
